<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br><br>
When you use another person&#8217;s ideas or words in your writing, include the author&#8217;s name immediately following the cited material. The authorâ€™s name should lead the reader to the respective entry in your Works Cited list. 
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip;was found to be the case (Smith).
</blockquote>
<br>
If your Works Cited list includes two authors with the same surname, include the first initial.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	&hellip; was found to be the case (A. Smith).
</blockquote>
<br>
Or include the author&#8217;s name in your sentence.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith suggests that &#34;the default position is markedly affected&#34;.
</blockquote>
